<b>Multi-task learning</b> is an approach to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../488/233488.xml">
machine learning</link>, that learns a problem together with other related problems at the same time, using a shared representation.  This often leads to a better model for the main task, because it allows the learner to use the commonality among the tasks.  Therefore, multi-task learning is a kind of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../550/3920550.xml">
inductive transfer</link>.
